      <div class="gk-article">
       <h1 class="article-header">
        People
       </h1>
       <p style="text-align: justify;">
        <strong>
         Giles Piriri - Chief Executive Officer
        </strong>
        <br />
        <br />
        Giles has 16 years' experience in the finance, banking investment industry in PNG, and is a senior Associate of the Financial Services Institute of Australasia and an Associate Member of the PNG Institute of Directors. Giles has served on the Management of the National Development Bank, the Investment Committee for Nambawan Super Limited, and the management team of BSP Capital. He has learnt from industry leaders at each of these institutions, increasing his technical competency, leadership qualities and knowledge.
        <br />
        <br />
        During his well-regarded career, Giles has been responsible for research and due diligence, investment, portfolio management / allocation of capital, monitoring of performance, and risk management and regulatory compliance. He implemented loan investment policies for the National Development Bank, andÂ  managed investment strategies for large accumulation and defined benefit superannuation funds such as Nambawan super, Nasfund, AON Master Trust, Defence Force Retirement Benefit Fund, and the Teachers Savings &amp; Loans Society.
       </p>
       <p style="text-align: justify;">
        Giles has also been involved in structuring major private and public capital raising deals and large syndicated debt financing, as well as listing companies on the port Moresby Stock Exchange.
        <br />
        <br />
        Giles holds a Master's degree in International Banking and Finance from the Durham Business school, United kingdom and a Bachelor's degree in Economics from the university of PNG, and has undertaken postgraduate studies in economics &amp; Bank management at the university of sydney.
        <br />
        <br />
        <strong>
         Yamyam Gire - General Manager
        </strong>
        <br />
        <br />
        Yamyam has almost 20 years' commercial and investment experience. He has had managerial roles with Nasfund, BSP Capital and Capital Stockbrokers, and is an Associate Member of the Financial ServiCes Institute of Australasia and a Member of PNG Institute of Directors.
        <br />
        <br />
        During his respected career across the commerical and finance industries, Yamyam has been responsible for investment due diligence, allocation of funds / portfolio management, performance monitoring / benchmarking, and marketing and regulatory risk management. He has created and implemented the investment strategies of a number of superannuation funds including Nasfund, AON Master Trust, former Sios workers Ritaia Fund, former OTML superannuation Fund and several savings and loan societies investments.
        <br />
        <br />
        Yamyam is currently studying for a Diploma in Financial Advising at the Financial Services Institute of Australia (FINSIA). He holds a certificate in Business Administration from International Management Centre, a Certificate in management II from PNG Institute of banking and a certificate on Essential Knowledge for Directors from Papua New Guinea Institute of Directors.
        <br />
        <br />
        <strong>
         Jeffrey Kunjil - Senior Investment Analyst
        </strong>
        <br />
        <br />
        Jeffrey has 8 years' experience in the finance, funds management and investment industry in PNG, and is a Member of Certified Practicing Accountants of PNG and an Associate Member of the Financial Services Institute of Australasia.
        <br />
        <br />
        Starting his career as an accountant, jeffrey brings an audit perspective to due diligence and compliance with client and regulatory requirements. He is also highly skilled at modelling financial spread-sheets and writing reports. Although specialising in the PNG property market Whilst Working at Kina Funds Management and BSP capital, jeffrey was responsible for managing various parts of the portfolios of Nambawan Super, AON Master trust, and the Defence Force Retirement Benefit Fund.
        <br />
        <br />
        Jeffrey holds a Bachelor's Degree in Accountancy (with a minor in Economics) and a Diploma in Business Administration from the University of Papua New Guinea, as well as a Certificate in Cost Benefit Analysis.
        <br />
        <br />
        <strong>
         JohnKevau - Investment Consultant
        </strong>
        <br />
        <br />
        John has 8 years experience in the finance, funds management and investment industry in PNG, and is a registered stockbroker and an Associate Member of the Financial Services Institute of Australasia.
        <br />
        starting his career as a stock broker at BSP Capital, John became the premier stockbroker in PNG. Recognised for his ability to pick value investments, he was then asked by Pac wealth to be their Chief Investment Officer until recently he worked with PNG sustainable Development program (PNGSDP) as the Investment Manager managing the domestic portion of the PNGSDP portfolio.
        <br />
        <br />
        John holds a Bachelor's Degree in Economics and Business from the University of Papua New Guinea, and is completing Macquaire University's Master of Applied Finance.
        <br />
        <br />
        <strong>
         Dean Williams - Investment Consultant
        </strong>
        <br />
        <br />
        Dean has extensive experience in investment markets globally, having worked in port Moresby, Sydney, Singapore, Tokyo and the United states. His appointments include trading currency and equity
        <br />
        derivatives, investing in private and public companies, managing a fund-of-fund. During his 20 year career, Dean has researched companies, industries, management, financial products and asset classes. He has profitably managed three K2b portfolios. Clients of his advisory company include a number of financial institutions, including BSP capital, Westpac and Bank of Queensland. He has also led a number of performance audits, including QIC (a K120B fund) and Brisbane City Council's Major Infrastructure projects office (which manages all bridges, tunnels,etc.).
        <br />
        <br />
        Dean is a certified Practicing Accountant, Certified Financial Planner, holds Master Degrees in Applied Finance and Financial planning and has taught economics and accounting at several universities.
        <br />
        His industry Fellowships include the Financial Services Institute of Australia, the Australian Insitutue of Mangement, and the Australian Institute of Company Directors, Where he is a judge on its premier Mastering the Boardroom program.
        <br />
        <br />
        <strong>
         Geoff Leo Ping Hui - Investment consultant
        </strong>
        <br />
        <br />
        Geoff has extensive experience spanning 40 years in investment markets globally, having worked with Pembroke Josephson Wright Limited as Private Client Advisor, Ord Minnett Limited as Senior Investment Advisor, Mclntosh Securities / Merrill Lynch Equities Private as Brisbane Office Manager. Geoff also held managerial positions with BNP Paribas Equities Private as Queensland State manager. Prior to being appointed as Queenland State Manager he held the position of Head of private Clients - Queensland and private client Advisor with BNP paribas equities.
        <br />
        <br />
        Geoff currently holds the position of Division Director, Pacific Islands Region, Macquarie private wealth - Macquarie Bank and is presently looking after the financial affaris of MRL Capital Limited having been with them since their days with MRDC. He has close business relationships with many landowner groups and trading houses in PNG as well as BSP Capital stockbrokers.
        <br />
        <br />
        Geoff holds a Bachelor's Degree in Economics (Accounting and Economics) from Universtiy of Sydney and holds the series 7 Accreditation (Us Market from NASDAQ / New York Stock Exchange). Geoff has extensive experience in project Finance, IPO's and corporate Advisory, Assets and Funds Mangement, promotion of financial products and services via PNG broking houses and banks. His interest also lies in helping landowner groups.
        <br />
        <br />
        <br />
        <br />
        <br />
       </p>
